  "texts": [
    "Instruction-tuned datasets like Alpaca, HellaSwag, and ARC could help further validate the generality of DRaFT-Q across diverse prompting formats and instruction-following styles.From a technical perspective, DRaFT-Q could benefit from enhancements in rank allocation criteria and reward computation.",
    "Currently, rank adaptation relies on exponentially smoothed curvature signals, and reward weighting is externally applied based on static heuristics.",
    "More advanced mechanisms such as reinforcement learning, adaptive reward learning, or gradient-based reward shaping could provide more granular control over token importance and capacity allocation.",
    "This opens the door to a new class of PEFT algorithms that unify learning dynamics, architecture adaptation, and semantic supervision.In future work, we plan to scale DRaFT-Q to larger models such as LLaMA-2-70B using A100/H100 clusters or Colossal-AI-style pipeline parallelism.",
    "We also aim to integrate DRaFT-Q with reinforcement learning from human feed-back (RLHF), adapter routing, and symbolic reasoning modules."
  ],
